==English==

'''Your Majesty'''

#A title of respect used when addressing a [[monarch]] of higher rank than a [[prince]]; that is, a [[king]], [[queen]], [[emperor]], or [[empress]].

==== Usage note ====
*This is the [[second-person]] form of address.  The forms used in the [[third person]] are [[His Majesty]] (for a king or emperor) and [[Her Majesty]] (for a queen or empress).

*If the reigning monarch is a prince or princess, the form is '''[[Your Highness]]'''.

*The exact forms vary somewhat from country to country.

